            <ObservedData>
              <Attribute Type="Description">In a boy, born of consanguineous parents of Moroccan descent (family 3, R14-22173), with intellectual developmental disorder with abnormal behavior, microcephaly, and short stature (IDDABS; 618342), de Brouwer et al. (2018) identified a homozygous deletion of 92-bp, comprising all of exon 15, in the PUS7 gene (NM_019042.3), resulting in a frameshift and premature termination that removes the C terminus, including 56 amino acid residues of the TruD catalytic domain. The premature stop codon is located after the last exon-exon boundary, and was demonstrated to escape nonsense-mediated mRNA in patient-derived cells. Levels of PUS7 mRNA were similar to controls, but Western blot analysis confirmed the absence of a normal-sized PUS7 protein. The variant was found by CNV analysis and multiplex amplification quantification analysis. The heterozygous deletion was present in the unaffected father and absent in an unaffected brother, but DNA from the mother was not available.</Attribute>
